    "created_at": "2015-04-22T02:23:55Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-04-22T15:46:15Z",
    "body": "Just wanted to state that it looks like this is still an issue in version 0.193. I installed Chrome 42 to see if it was exhibiting similar behavior when launched with the `--force-device-scale-factor=2.0` flag, and it does. All menus seem to be double the size that they should be (for a total of 4x scaling, I guess?). \n\nLooks like we have to wait for Chrome/Chromium to get things sorted out.\n\nUpdate:\n\nJust out of curiosity, I installed Chrome versions 43 (currently beta) and 44 (currently unstable). Both seem to work properly on my Gnome Shell / Gentoo box, so it looks like a fix may be coming soon.\n"
