    "created_at": "2015-09-10T23:26:11Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-09-10T23:28:48Z",
    "body": "I have this problem too.\n\nThe recent Chromium version update made the text in the menus actually visible, before you couldn't see the options due to the large size causing the text to go outside the visible area, making Atom basically unusable (unless you don't need the menus).\n\nNow the menus are still huge, but the options are visible despite their size.\n\nToo bad --force-device-scale-factor=1 doesn't seem to do anything. I wonder if their is another way to force it.\n"
